{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G4 child-consistency audit — parent safe-luge-nog/b4d4-3369-6dd2-41e6, THIS child (908c link-consumer) vs whole roster (908c + ba2c parent-consumer)]\n\nChecked the 7 cross-child interaction modes; all clean (high-confidence, benign-reading filter applied):\n\n1. Implicit shared state — `managed_refs` + `should_propagate_removal` are EXPLICITLY parent-owned shared state, declared in parent What/Scope. Both children only READ the gate/set; the reducer fold + serialization is parent in-scope work. No hidden/undeclared shared mutation. Verified `managed_refs` does not yet exist in tree (parent builds it). CLEAN.\n\n2. Conflicting assumptions — gate semantics agree across parent + both children: peer ref present + locally absent => REMOVE iff in managed_refs, else ADOPT inbound; local-authoritative, NO inbound-remove dual. 908c (\"NO inbound-remove dual ... consistent with parent\") matches ba2c (CLEAR only when in managed_refs, else ADOPT) and parent's `should_propagate_removal` definition. CLEAN.\n\n3. Dependency gap — 908c logically depends on the parent primitive/gate existing; the parent-child hierarchy (b4d4 is the parent ticket building it) supplies that ordering, and parent Scope explicitly tracks the two CONSUMERS as children. No undeclared gap. CLEAN.\n\n4. Scope overlap — 908c touches the LINK path (`_diff_links`, new acli `delete_relationship`, batch_dispatch link REMOVE, inbound link-ADD suppression); sibling ba2c touches the PARENT-CLEAR path (`_map_local_to_jira_fields`/emit_detach_clear). Disjoint code paths. Shared gate is common CONSUMPTION, not duplicated logic. Verified root-cause cites against code: outbound `_diff_links` ADD-only (outbound_differ.py:1002-1040), inbound `_diff_links_inbound` ADD-only (inbound_differ.py:440-514) — accurate. CLEAN.\n\n5. Ordering violation — 908c and ba2c are independent consumers (links vs parent); no inter-child ordering dependency; both gated behind the parent primitive. CLEAN.\n\n6. Consumer impact — both children add same-pass suppression in the inbound differ, but on DISJOINT ref kinds (908c: link-ADD echo; ba2c: parent adoption). No cross-interference. CLEAN.\n\n7. Residual references — 908c references parent alias \"safe-luge-nog\"; confirmed b4d4's alias IS safe-luge-nog. No stale/dangling reference. CLEAN.\n\nResult: no high-confidence cross-child interaction defect. Parent + this child are consistent. G4 CLEAN (empty findings).\n\n(Note for author, NON-G4 — single-child internal underspecification, not a cross-child contradiction: the Jira \"Blocks\" type collapses both `blocks` and `depends_on` logical kinds direction-agnostically (inbound_differ.py:497-502; outbound dedup adds both inward/outward keys at outbound_differ.py:995-998), while `managed_refs` keys on direction-distinguished `(kind, target)`. The link-REMOVE gate-lookup against a direction-collapsed Jira link vs direction-keyed managed_refs is unspecified. Flagged here only as context; it is a G2-class within-child gap, not a G4 finding.)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782536998634082001,"uuid":"0d185615-ec60-4ef8-af14-b70883635542"}